        }
      },
      {
        "id": "BXnUUTGklhoUs_dv",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ol><li>What does n represent?</li><li>What information does the equation –4 + n = 45 represent?</li><li>What is the new temperature?</li><li>Suppose the temperature dropped from 45°F to –4°F. How would you represent this on the number line? An equation?</li><li>How is the sign of the change in temperature reflected on the number line? Equation?</li></ol>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "_oTIZIdHwouG7Rww",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation B. Matching Representations for Temperature Change </strong></p><p>The temperature change for six days is represented on a number line and with an equation. </p><p>Match the number line and equation that represents the change in each Day. What is the change?</p><ul><li>Sunday: 20°F to –10°F</li><li>Monday: –20°F to –10°F</li><li>Tuesday: –20°F to 10°F</li><li>Wednesday: –10°F to –20°F</li><li>Thursday: 20°F to 10°F</li><li>Friday: 10°F to 20°F</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
